				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">DirectDraw provides horrible vblank waiting code, then SDL uses that horrible vblank waiting code.</div><br />Is there a standard workaround to this without dropping Windows altogether?</div>
<br />
<br />Prior to migrating my emulator to DX10 (where the problem has, apparently,  been fixed), I would time the frame emulation and, if there were more than x milliseconds left before the next frame, I'd make a Sleep() call. The default granularity of Sleep() is 10ms, but if you want more accurate timing, it's possible to reduce it with another API call (don't remember what that call is...). Worked reasonably well.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />get nemulator
